@NODE "what" "What's YAG_Genesis"
@NEXT install
@PREV main
@{B}What's YAG_Genesis ?@{UB}

This is another GUI dedicated to Amigenerator, or I could say Yet another ! :)
It was written for those who do not like "All-in-one" GUI (such as the great
Nostalgia) or simply never found a GUI with theses main features:

- Preview of the selected game (screenshot or anything else)
- Rom informations (Rom name, copyright and version)
- you can select your Amigenrator executable
- All amigenerator parameters configurables and bubble help described
- Fully localised
- Activate or De-activate GUI elements (preview, rom info, status)


@ENDNODE
@NODE "install" "How to install"
@NEXT req
@PREV what
@{B}How to (Un)Install it ?@{UB}

Well, I'll never do easier: simply click the installer icon to install, or the
unInstaller icone to remove !

@ENDNODE
@NODE "req" "Requierments"
@NEXT preview
@PREV install
@{B}Requierments@{UB}

- MUI 3.8 (not tested on earlier version)
- Guigfx.library and GuiGfx for MUI
- Amigenerator (no sense without :)
- a PCX Datatype
- some roms (Rom infos feature only work with ".bin" roms)
@ENDNODE
@NODE "preview" "preview"
@NEXT historic
@PREV requierments
@{B}How to make preview ?@{UB}

Well in fact it's quite simple: to show a preview, the program just search for
"The_Name_Of_the_Rom.pcx" in the same directory as the rom file. unlike the the
signification of the ".pcx" extension, the picture can be of any format as it
use datatypes.

So why PCX ? Because by default, Amigenerator save it screenshots in this format !
@ENDNODE
@NODE "historic" "Historic"
@NEXT FAQ
@PREV req
@{B}Historic@{UB}

V 1.0 : First public release !
@ENDNODE
@NODE "FAQ" "F.A.Q"
@NEXT future
@PREV historic
@{B}Frequently Asked Question:@{UB}

@{B}Q: Why with some roms, the "rom informations" section is empty ?@{UB}

R: Rom informations only exists on bin (.bin) file. The smd files are
    not pure images files and have to be converted by the emulator
    before starting the emulation.

    Note: You can convert your smd file in bin by using the tools
             smd2bin that I wrote on aminet.


@{B}Q: Why after having selected a screen mode, the emulation does@{UB}
@{B}    not start ?@{UB}

R: You must choose a screenMode with a width of 320. I've done
    a filter, but MUI does not seem to keep it in mind when opening
    the ASL requester... :(
@ENDNODE
